  "title": "",
  "body": " frequency table   A frequency table is a two-column table used to summarize the distribution of a qualitative (categorical) variable.   The first column lists the distinct categories or values that the variable can take.    The second column shows the frequency, or the number of times each category occurs in the dataset.      "
